Date:  0/0/1962
Source:  Australian & NZ English [TS]
Author:  SYDER & HODGETTS
Vol / Page:  519
Edition:
Quote:  This is a happy state of affairs; any and every difficulty is now past; good luck attends and the enterprise will continue to prosper, as it is now doing. .in 4;`He put in the irrigation; there was a lot of hard work but now buyers come from everywhere for his garden-stuff and he's getting rich fast. He's home on the pig's back.' P: <i>home on the pig's back </i>very successful!; thoroughly (and easily) ca1910: a catchphrase, mostly among NZders and Australians.
