Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGiLL
Vol / Page:  57
Edition:
Quote:  <i>home on the pig's back</i> very successful or easy; eg `if this horse wins, we're home on the pig's back.' Mostly NZA.
